AGI - At least eight people were injured at night in a Ukrainian air strike against the Russian city of Belgorod and its surroundings. It has made known the regional governor Vyacheslav Gladkov. "The city and district of Belgorod were targeted by an air strike by the Ukrainian armed forces. Residential buildings and cars were hit directly", wrote Gladkov on Telegram.
&nbsp;
"According to the first information, eight people were injured: seven adults and one child," added the Russian governor. Five of these people, including an 11-year-old girl, were wounded by the splinters and were hospitalized, while the other three were cured on the spot. According to the governor in the city of Belgorod 19 condominiums were damaged including 34 apartments and 37 vehicles.&nbsp;

